[6] Norovirus, hotel - Canada (BC): suspected
Date: 31 May 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Montreal Gazette, Mon 31 May 2004 [edited]
<http://www.canada.com/montreal/montrealgazette/news/story.html?id=79c13619-83c0-465c-a346-31d182d565b2>


Canada: Norovirus suspected as Cause of Outbreak at Yoho Nations Park
--------------------------------------------------
The virus that shut down a hotel in a national park in British
Columbia after almost 200 people suffered severe vomiting and
diarrhea is probably a strain of norovirus. The symptoms - a sudden
outbreak that quickly infected many people in only 4 days -- are
hallmarks of the virus, said John Blatherwick, the chief medical
officer of Vancouver Coastal Health. Guests at Emerald Lake Lodge, a
hotel in Yoho National Park, first reported health problems Tuesday.
Hotel staff also fell ill, leading its owners to ask Health Canada to
investigate. As the epidemic grew to about 150 people by Friday, the
hotel voluntarily closed.

